  "source": "Numerics/Data/Interpolation/Support/Search.cs; no dedicated Test_Search.cs exists upstream (grep-confirmed across Test_Numerics), and no other test file exercises Search.Sequential/Search.Bisection with a hardcoded literal (Histogram's Test_Indexing exercises GetBinIndexOf, which calls Bisection internally, but through Histogram -- see histogram.json), so every case here is curated.",
  "reference": "Numerics @ a2c4dbf. Args convention (this port's own -- see fixtures/README.md): args = [values..., x, start] (n = len(args) - 2), the default SortOrder.Ascending only (the only order exercised by any real caller -- SNIS.cs always calls Search.Sequential with the default order, and Histogram.GetBinIndexOf always calls Search.Bisection with the default order too; see search.hpp's header comment for the descending-order Bisection quirk this does NOT exercise). Probes cover both boundary sentinels (below/above the range, exact first/last-element match) and interior lookups, including one with a non-zero `start` to exercise the scan-from/bracket-from-start behavior both algorithms share. Every value was generated by running the case's inputs through tools/oracle_emitter --dump against the REAL C# Search class and confirming the printed actuals reproduce via verify_oracles.py.",
